i started out actually obese, but i‚Äôm not thin now, just average. i started at a BMI of 41, now i‚Äôm at 23. i‚Äôve gone from BMI 41 to 24 to 33 and back down to 23 now. i‚Äôve gotten so many positive comments during the times i‚Äôm in the process of losing weight. first time around, everyone made comments about how small i was getting and how great i looked. i was also treated better by the people i would interact with on a day to day basis when i lost weight compared to how i was treated when i was bigger, people were just overall nicer to me. then i started gaining some weight back and nobody made any nice compliments about me and then i started losing weight again and the comments about how i look like i lost weight and how i looked small started happening as if that‚Äôs a compliment in and of itself. i mean i‚Äôll take it as one bc i want to be tiny, but i also know deep down that saying you look skinny or small really isn‚Äôt a compliment.
